    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>linguine</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>linguine</strong> for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite, then drain it, reserving a cup of <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Reboil half a kettle</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>and <strong>soft cheese</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>creamy stock</strong></p>",
